FBIS3-51518 "drlat014_r_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 Peru Fujimori, U.S. Envoy Discuss Human Rights Situation Justice Minister Calls Dialogue `Smooth' PA2101023494 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 20 Jan 94 PA2101023494 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "Newspaper of the Airwaves" newscast] [Text] President Alberto Fujimori and Alexander Watson, U.S. assistant secretary of state for Inter-American affairs, have discussed democracy, human rights, and drug trafficking. Justice Minister Fernando Vega Santagadea explained that the dialogue was smooth and that there were no points of disagreement: [Begin recording] Mr. Watson knows Peru's political and social situation very well. The dialogue went smoothly. There were no points of disagreement. Every topic was discussed, particularly the administration of justice, human rights, the administration of jails, and drug trafficking. They also discussed the upcoming summit of heads of state proposed by the United States for the second half of 1994. The meeting is to be held in the United States, but details will have to be furnished by Mr. Watson in person. I will meet with Watson's delegation tomorrow to discuss the justice problem. [end recording]
